- Install kpack: https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/blob/master/docs/tutorial.md

```
kubectl apply -f release-0.1.2.yaml
```

- Create values.yaml

```

$ cat > values.yml <<EOF

system_domain: mydomain.example.com
services:
  router:
    type: LoadBalancer
  tcp-router:
    type: LoadBalancer
  ssh-proxy:
    type: LoadBalancer

kpack:
  registry_username: dockerhub_username
  registry_password: dockerhub_password
  registry_server: https://index.docker.io/v1/
  workloads_namespace: eirini
  builder_namespace: eirini-staging
  registry_service_account_name: kpack-service-account
  registry_tag_base: dockerhub_username

features:
  eirini:
    enabled: true

install_stacks:
  - sle15
EOF

$ expose VALUES=$PWD/values.yml
```

- Install minio (for blobstore)

https://github.com/minio/charts

```
$ kubectl create ns minio
$ helm repo add minio https://helm.min.io/
$ # TODO: don't hardcode access key and secret. Use quarkssecret to generate one.
$ # https://github.com/minio/charts#existing-secret
$ # This secret should also be created in the opi namespace (so it can be mounted in the cc pod)
$ kubectl create secret generic -n minio minio-secret --from-literal=accesskey=admin --from-literal=secretkey=12345678
$ helm install minio --namespace minio minio/minio --set existingSecret=minio-secret
```

- Install kubecf:

```
make all
```
